The information suggests a functional organization for ABC Corp. This structure works well for stable organizations with well-defined roles and duties that need specialized skills. Functional structures organize personnel by function, such as manufacturing, marketing, or finance. The CEO would handle a few people personally. These supervisors would supervise firm functions. Low-level staff would mostly follow upper supervisors' routines and make few decisions. ABC Corp. sells mostly to other firms, works in a stable environment, and has a distinct product range. With just 20 people, the firm would be simple to run and enable the CEO to communicate with the rest of the organization. 